E WALL 8TREET KIND.\n\u2022t It It\nBy WILLIAM B. R1DGELY. Comptroller of ttia Currency.\nThe announcement made by Secretary Cortelyou of his\nrelieving the strain on the money market by the deposit of govern\u00ad\nment funds is VERY WISE AND TIMELY and should go very\nfar toward allaying apprehension and restoring business to its normal\ncondition.\nWHILE THE PRESENT 8ITUATI0N IS ONE REQUIRING CARE\nAND COOL HEADED, DELIBERATE ACTION, ESPECIALLY ON THE\nPART OF THE BANKS, THERE IS NO REASON AT ALL WHY THE\nDEMAND FOR LIQUIDATION SHOULD SO SPREAD A8 TO PRODUCE\nANYTHING LIKE A PANIC OR COMMERCIAL CRISI8.\nThe banking condition is UNUSUALLY SOUND, more so on\naccount of the readjustment of stock market values.\nNational Control of\nIndustry Is Inevitable.\nBy Dr. CHARLES J. BUSHNELL. Sociologist, of Washington.\nHE modern trust is the response under individualistic condi\u00ad\ntions to the inevitable demand for a MORE UNIFIED\nAND ECONOMICAL business organization. And Social\u00ad\nism itself, with all its past faults and failures, is but the\nFURTHER EFFORT to carry the will of the people effectively into\nour industrial as well as our political life.\nBY ITS DEMAND THAT WE SHOULD OWN AND CONTROL\nCOLLECTIVELY WHAT WE NEED TO USE COLLECTIVELY, SOCIAL\u00ad\nISM IS A PROTEST AGAINST THE THEORY THAT ALL A WORK\nINGMAN NEEDS AND WANTS IS A ROOF, A FAMILY AND A FULL\nDINNER PAIL. IT IS AN ASPIRATION FOR A FULLER AND\nNOBLER 80CIAL LIFE.\nFor one I believe that the present UNDENIABLE DECAY 01*\nDEMOCRATIC INSTITUTIONS, of government of, for and bv\nthe people, is temporary and is slowly arousing a reaction which is\nbound to lead us into a finer and a broader national life, with adequate\nNATIONAL CONTROL of our great industries.\nAmerica Not the\nLand of the Free.\nBy Sir CASPAR PUROON CLARKE* Director\nS&Qh\n4\"\ni.\nS\"\nithree\nUR farms produce more th^n $6,500,000,000 per an-%\nnum, and THE PROSPECT IS GOOD for an av\u00ad\nerage crop. Our mines yield more than $1,500,000,\n000 and our forests more than $1,000,000,000. And\nneither of these sources of wealth has been exhausted:\nThe output of our factories in other than food prod\u00ad\nucts is approximately $12,000,000,000, and no fires have been extin\u00ad\nguished.\nThe railways earn more than $2,000,000,000, and THEY ABE\nALL IN SUCCESSFUL OPERATION. The payrolls of our facto\u00ad\nries and railways aggregate approximately $3,500,000,000, and the\nscale of wages has not been reduced.\nIN OTHER WORD8, THE REAL SOURCES OF THE PEOPLE'S\nWEALTH HAVE NOT YET BEEN AFFECTED, AND THE ABILITY OF\nINDUSTRIAL CONCERNS TO PAY DIVIDENDS IS NOT MEA8URED\nBY THE MARKET PRICE OF THEIR STOCKS.\nBy HENRY C. FRICK of the United States Steel Corporation.\nI FIND NOTHING IN UNDERLYING CONDITIONS TO WARRANT\nTHE APPARENT GREAT LACK OF CONFIDENCE IN BUSINE83 GEN\u00ad\nERALLY WHICH NOW SEEM8 PREVALENT. IF THERE 18 ANY\u00ad\nTHING TO JUSTIFY THAT FEELING IN TRADE CONDITIONS, I\nDO NOT SEE IT.\nI can understand the VAGUE, BUT REAL UNSETTXEMENT\nOF SENTIMENT created by current agitation against corporations,\nbut this is in a measure apart from real conditions and is capable of\ncorrection. I believe myself, and always have, in the correction of\nABUSES, WHETHER CORPORATE OR INDIVIDUAL, but I\nfeel that such care should be exercised in doing this that only the\nwrongdoer should suffer.\nof\nof Art, New York.\nTALK ABOUT OPPRE88ION IN RU88IA! WHERE WILL YOU\nFIND ANY GREATER OPPRESSION THAN IN THE STATE OF\nMAINE, WITH 1T8 UNJU8T BLUE LAWST FREEDOM! AMERICA\nCANNOT BOAST OF THAT.\nIt is WOMEN WHO ARE REALLY AT THE\nOF THESE BLUE RIBBON LAWS, these tyrannical restrictions\nof persona! liberty. Whenever a woman permits her emotions to run\naway with her judgment she is almost sure to rush into something\nat\nthis kind. Women are all right until thev become FADDISTS.\nmmmm\nmi\nthe MctropoUttn Miimiin\nMERICA is not the land of liberty. Your blue ribbon laws\nthat make the temperate suffer for the intemperate are most\nTYRANNICAL. In England at least we have no laws in\u00ad\nterfering with personal rights.\n~isi\u00a7|S\n5\n'A,\n1\ntm\nV-p\n'4i\nBOTTOM\nv{\n-1\nI\nplan\nfor\nti\nis\nsr\nv.-\n'IK\n\u00a7&I","height":"27127","width":"19140"}}
